SIMPLE: hush
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hush
<hw>Hush</hw> <pr>(h⟦ucr⟧sh)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Hushed</conjf> <pr>(h⟦ucr⟧sht)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Hushing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>huschen</ets>, <ets>hussen</ets>, prob. of imitative origin; cf.
LG. <ets>hussen</ets> to lull to sleep, G. <ets>husch</ets> quick, make
haste, be silent.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To still; to silence; to calm;
to make quiet; to repress the noise or clamor of.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>My tongue shall <qex>hush</qex> again this storm of war.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To appease; to allay; to calm; to soothe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With thou, then,⟦br⟧
<qex>Hush</qex> my cares?</q> <rj><qau>Otway.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And <qex>hush'd</qex> my deepest grief of all.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To hush up</b></col>, <cd>to procure silence concerning;
to suppress; to keep secret.</cd> ⟦ldquo⟧This matter is <xex>hushed
up</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Pope.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hush</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hush
<hw>Hush</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To become or to keep still or
quiet; to become silent; -- esp. used in the imperative, as an
exclamation; be still; be silent or quiet; make no noise.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Hush</qex>, idle words, and thoughts of ill.</q>
<rj><qau>Keble.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But all these strangers' presence every one did
<qex>hush</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hush</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Hush
<hw>Hush</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Stillness; silence; quiet.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧It is the <xex>hush</xex> of night.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Byron.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hush money</b></col>, <cd>money paid to secure silence,
or to prevent the disclosure of facts.</cd>
<rj><au>Swift.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hush</ent>⟦br⟧

